    <abstract abstract-type="teaser" id="abs0025">
      <p>Arnol et al. present a statistical method for analyzing single-cell expression data in a spatial context. The method identifies the sources of gene expression variability by decomposing it into different components, each attributable to a different source. These sources include aspects of spatial variation, in particular cell-cell interactions.</p>
